			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Often linking nacl_bootstrap causes my laptop to swap to death and become unresponsive.  If I press Ctrl-C, the machine might become usable after 5 or 10 minutes of swapping.  My laptop has 4Gb of memory and tends to have high memory pressure generally.

I imagine that BFD ld is consuming a lot of memory as a result of the tricks we're using for building an executable that reserves 1Gb of address space.
